citations:
    citation-agot-sansa-v:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Sansa V"
            text_from_source: "Ser Barristan looked up sharply. 'A hall to die in, and men to bury me. I thank you, my lords … but I spit upon your pity.' He reached up and undid the clasps that held his cloak in place, and the heavy white garment slithered from his shoulders to fall in a heap on the floor. 'I am a knight,' he told them."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "First court session of Joffrey's reign in the throne room. Grand Maester Pycelle reads decrees: Tywin Lannister named Hand of the King; Cersei Lannister seated on the small council; Janos Slynt elevated to lord and granted Harrenhal, seated on the small council. Barristan Selmy dismissed from the Kingsguard — he strips off his armor and vows to die a knight. Sandor Clegane (the Hound) appointed to the Kingsguard in Selmy's place (notably not a knight). Jaime Lannister named Lord Commander of the Kingsguard in absentia. Sansa publicly pleads for her father's life; Joffrey says he will spare Ned if Ned confesses. Lords named as traitors include: Stannis, Renly, both Royces, Ser Loras Tyrell, Lord Mace Tyrell, Thoros of Myr, Beric Dondarrion, Lysa Arryn, Hoster Tully, Edmure, Brynden Tully, Jason Mallister, Bryce Caron, Tytos Blackwood, Walder Frey and heir Stevron, Karyl Vance, Jonos Bracken, Shella Whent, Doran Martell and sons, Lady Catelyn, Robb, Bran, Rickon, and Arya Stark."
